Summaries for ADSS Gene

Entrez Gene Summary for ADSS Gene

  • This gene encodes the enzyme adenylosuccinate synthetase which catalyzes the first committed step in the conversion of inosine monophosphate to adenosine monophosphate. A pseudogene of this gene is found on chromosome 17.[provided by RefSeq, Nov 2010]

GeneCards Summary for ADSS Gene

ADSS (Adenylosuccinate Synthase) is a Protein Coding gene. Among its related pathways are Alanine, aspartate and glutamate metabolism and Metabolism. GO annotations related to this gene include GTP binding and phosphate ion binding. An important paralog of this gene is ADSSL1.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for ADSS Gene

  • PURA2_HUMAN,P30520

  • Plays an important role in the de novo pathway and in the salvage pathway of purine nucleotide biosynthesis. Catalyzes the first committed step in the biosynthesis of AMP from IMP.

No data available for Tocris Summary , Gene Wiki entry , PharmGKB "VIP" Summary , fRNAdb sequence ontologies and piRNA Summary for ADSS Gene
